            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1368998322,
            "creation_date": 1368998322,
            "body": "<p><code>read()<\/code> is doing exactly what it's <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/Reader.html#read%28%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">supposed to<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Reads a <strong>single<\/strong> character. This method will block until a character is available, an I/O error occurs, or the end of the stream is reached.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>(emphasis added)<\/p>\n\n<p>Instead, you can call <code>BufferedReader.readLine()<\/code> in a loop.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 16639577,
            "question_id": 16639550
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2f0d9dec16bae1e06552af55ddefc11f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 277416,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 571407,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/571407/jb-nizet",
                "reputation": 694302,
                "display_name": "JB Nizet",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1368998327,
            "creation_date": 1368998327,
            "body": "<p>As <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/BufferedReader.html#read%28%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">the javadoc<\/a> indicates, the read() method reads a single char, and returns it as an int (in order to be able to return -1 to indicate the end of the stream). To print the int as a char, just cast it:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int c = reader.read();\nif (c != -1) {\n    System.out.println((char) c);\n}\nelse {\n    System.out.println(\"end of the stream\");\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>To read everything, loop until you get -1, or read line by line until you get null.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 16639578,
            "question_id": 16639550
        }
